<emphasis id="CA82EAEE4970FF9165D5FADAFEEBFA90" bold="true" box="[199,335,1362,1387]" pageId="1" pageNumber="238">Comments.</emphasis>
When 
<bibRefCitation id="9C674B0D4970FF9164B0FADBFD8AFA90" author="Levy" box="[418,558,1363,1387]" pageId="1" pageNumber="238" refString="Levy, G. (1998) The ground-spider genera Setaphis, Trachyzelotes, Zelotes, and Drassyllus (Araneae: Gnaphosidae) in Israel. Israel Journal of Zoology, 44, 93 ‾ 158." type="journal article" year="1998">Levy (1998)</bibRefCitation>
recorded 
<taxonomicName id="3FF64D7F4970FF9167B2FADBFBC8FA90" authority="(O. P. Cambridge, 1872)" authorityName="O.P. Cambridge" authorityYear="1872" baseAuthorityName="O. P. Cambridge" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[672,1132,1362,1387]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Zelotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helvolus">
<emphasis id="CA82EAEE4970FF9167B2FADBFCF2FA90" box="[672,854,1363,1387]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="238">Zelotes helvolus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="9C674B0D4970FF91667AFADBFBC0FA90" author="Cambridge" box="[872,1124,1362,1387]" pageId="1" pageNumber="238" refString="Pickard-Cambridge, O. (1872). General list of the spiders of Palestine and Syria, with descriptions of numerous new species, and characters of two new genera. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 40, 212 ‾ 354." type="journal article" year="1872">O.P. Cambridge, 1872</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="80E1766C4970FF9161A1FADAFB50FA90" box="[1203,1268,1362,1387]" name="Israel" pageId="1" pageNumber="238">Israel</collectingCountry>
, he recognised that “ 
<taxonomicName id="3FF64D7F4970FF9165C9FAFFFEF9FA75" baseAuthorityName="O. P. Cambridge" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[219,349,1398,1422]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Zelotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helvolus">
<emphasis id="CA82EAEE4970FF9165C9FAFFFEF9FA75" box="[219,349,1398,1422]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="238">Z. helvolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares somatic characters of the genus but deviates to an extent from the general palpal configuration found in 
<emphasis id="CA82EAEE4970FF9164B2FA13FDA5FA48" box="[416,513,1435,1459]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="238">
<taxonomicName id="3FF64D7F4970FF9164B2FA13FE5CFA48" box="[416,504,1435,1459]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Zelotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Zelotes</taxonomicName>
”
</emphasis>
stating that he tentatively kept the species under an ”informal subgroup” of this genus. The specimens here determined as 
<taxonomicName id="3FF64D7F4970FF91676CFA37FD5FFA2D" baseAuthorityName="O. P. Cambridge" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[638,763,1470,1494]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Zelotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helvolus">
<emphasis id="CA82EAEE4970FF91676CFA37FD5FFA2D" box="[638,763,1470,1494]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="238">Z. helvolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have all the distinctive and other characters for the genus 
<emphasis id="CA82EAEE4970FF916585FA6BFE98FA00" box="[151,316,1507,1531]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="238">Cryprodrassus</emphasis>
Miller, 1943 (
<bibRefCitation id="9C674B0D4970FF9164F8FA6AFD37FA00" author="Murphy" box="[490,659,1506,1531]" pageId="1" pageNumber="238" refString="Murphy, J. (2007) Gnaphosid genera of the world. Uol. 1 &amp; 2. British Arachnological Society, St Neots, Cambridgeshire, 605 pp. [pp. i ‾ xii, 1 ‾ 92 &amp; i ‾ ii, 93 ‾ 605]" type="book" year="2007">Murphy, 2007</bibRefCitation>
), namely: small size and pale body colouration, characteristic eye configuration (PME largest and oval, all others round, AME smallest and with black surroundings), cheliceral dentition on both retro and prolateral margins (2̄4 on PM and 2̄3 on RM), large number of trichobothria on Ti, Mt and Ta, presence of large scutum on male abdomens, preening brushes on Mt III and IV. Also the general structure of the male palps (long, thick embolus tapering at its end, characteristic sclerotised conductor, small retrolateral tibial apophysis) as well as the female spermathecae with bipartite chambers are shared among all members of the genus. It is for this reason that 
<taxonomicName id="3FF64D7F4970FF9167D9F933FCEDF928" baseAuthorityName="O. P. Cambridge" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[715,841,1723,1747]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Zelotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helvolus">
<emphasis id="CA82EAEE4970FF9167D9F933FCEDF928" box="[715,841,1723,1747]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="238">Z. helvolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="3FF64D7F4970FF916105F933FB1EF928" box="[1047,1210,1723,1747]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Cryptodrassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CA82EAEE4970FF916105F933FB1EF928" box="[1047,1210,1723,1747]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="238">Cryptodrassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In his atlas of the 
<taxonomicName id="3FF64D7F4970FF916585F956FE4EF90C" authority=", Murphy (2007)" authorityName=", Murphy" authorityYear="2007" box="[151,490,1758,1783]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Gnaphosidae, 
<bibRefCitation id="9C674B0D4970FF916429F956FE4EF90C" author="Murphy" box="[315,490,1758,1783]" pageId="1" pageNumber="238" refString="Murphy, J. (2007) Gnaphosid genera of the world. Uol. 1 &amp; 2. British Arachnological Society, St Neots, Cambridgeshire, 605 pp. [pp. i ‾ xii, 1 ‾ 92 &amp; i ‾ ii, 93 ‾ 605]" type="book" year="2007">Murphy (2007)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
commented on differences between the 
<typeStatus id="274D885E4970FF9166D1F957FC57F90C" box="[963,1011,1759,1783]" pageId="1" pageNumber="238">type</typeStatus>
species of the genus, 
<taxonomicName id="3FF64D7F4970FF9161E8F957FEE6F8E0" authority="(Balogh, 1935)" authorityName="Balogh" authorityYear="1935" baseAuthorityName="Balogh" baseAuthorityYear="1935" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Cryptodrassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hungaricus">
<emphasis id="CA82EAEE4970FF9161E8F957FA38F90D" box="[1274,1436,1758,1782]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="238">C. hungaricus</emphasis>
(Balogh, 1935)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="3FF64D7F4970FF91646EF88BFD03F8E0" authority="Chatzaki, 2002" authorityName="Chatzaki" authorityYear="2002" box="[380,679,1794,1819]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Cryptodrassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="creticus">
<emphasis id="CA82EAEE4970FF91646EF88BFE51F8E1" box="[380,501,1795,1818]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="238">C. creticus</emphasis>
Chatzaki, 2002
</taxonomicName>
, mainly related to a difference in body size (
<taxonomicName id="3FF64D7F4970FF916184F88BFA90F8E0" baseAuthorityName="Balogh" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[1174,1332,1795,1819]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Cryptodrassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hungaricus">
<emphasis id="CA82EAEE4970FF916184F88BFA90F8E0" box="[1174,1332,1795,1819]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="238">C. hungaricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
less than 
<quantity id="3F0E9B194970FF916585F8AFFF7EF8C5" box="[151,218,1831,1855]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="238" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
, “ 
<taxonomicName id="3FF64D7F4970FF9165E1F8AFFEC8F8C5" authorityName="Chatzaki" authorityYear="2002" box="[243,364,1831,1854]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Cryptodrassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="creticus">
<emphasis id="CA82EAEE4970FF9165E1F8AFFEC8F8C5" box="[243,364,1831,1854]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="238">C. creticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” 
<quantity id="3F0E9B194970FF916492F8AEFE7EF8C4" box="[384,474,1830,1855]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="238" unit="mm" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3-5 mm</quantity>
) and in the PME (in 
<taxonomicName id="3FF64D7F4970FF9167DAF8AFFCC3F8C5" baseAuthorityName="Balogh" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[712,871,1830,1854]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Cryptodrassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hungaricus">
<emphasis id="CA82EAEE4970FF9167DAF8AFFCC3F8C5" box="[712,871,1830,1854]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="238">C. hungaricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
they are clearly larger than the rest of eyes and in 
<taxonomicName id="3FF64D7F4970FF916585F8C3FEB5F899" authorityName="Chatzaki" authorityYear="2002" box="[151,273,1867,1890]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Cryptodrassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="creticus">
<emphasis id="CA82EAEE4970FF916585F8C3FEB5F899" box="[151,273,1867,1890]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="238">C. creticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
they are only slightly larger). However, in the absence of adequate comparative material, and because “ 
<taxonomicName id="3FF64D7F4970FF9165B1F8E7FEBFF87D" authorityName="Chatzaki" authorityYear="2002" box="[163,283,1903,1926]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Cryptodrassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="creticus">
<emphasis id="CA82EAEE4970FF9165B1F8E7FEBFF87D" box="[163,283,1903,1926]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="238">C. creticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” still conforms to the generic characters, he did not create a new genus to include this species and two more from 
<collectingCountry id="80E1766C4970FF916409F81AFEFAF850" box="[283,350,1938,1963]" name="Spain" pageId="1" pageNumber="238">Spain</collectingCountry>
, one of which seems closer to 
<taxonomicName id="3FF64D7F4970FF9167DBF81BFCCFF850" baseAuthorityName="Balogh" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[713,875,1939,1963]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Cryptodrassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hungaricus">
<emphasis id="CA82EAEE4970FF9167DBF81BFCCFF850" box="[713,875,1939,1963]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="238">C. hungaricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the other closer to 
<taxonomicName id="3FF64D7F4970FF916196F81BFB5BF851" authorityName="Chatzaki" authorityYear="2002" box="[1156,1279,1939,1962]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Cryptodrassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="creticus">
<emphasis id="CA82EAEE4970FF916196F81BFB5BF851" box="[1156,1279,1939,1962]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="238">C. creticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. While a full revision of 
<taxonomicName id="3FF64D7F4970FF916407F83EFE1DF835" box="[277,441,1974,1998]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Cryptodrassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CA82EAEE4970FF916407F83EFE1DF835" box="[277,441,1974,1998]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="238">Cryptodrassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is clearly required to define its taxonomic status, more material is required to enable this. All material here treated as 
<taxonomicName id="3FF64D7F4970FF9164C1F853FDD2F808" box="[467,630,2011,2035]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Cryptodrassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CA82EAEE4970FF9164C1F853FDD2F808" box="[467,630,2011,2035]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="238">Cryptodrassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closer to the “subgroup” of 
<taxonomicName id="3FF64D7F4970FF9166C6F853FBE9F809" authorityName="Chatzaki" authorityYear="2002" box="[980,1101,2011,2034]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Cryptodrassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="creticus">
<emphasis id="CA82EAEE4970FF9166C6F853FBE9F809" box="[980,1101,2011,2034]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="238">C. creticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is noteworthy that the eye configuration (especially PME relative size, position and PME-PME interdistance) is variable and until more material of both sexes of all species becomes available, the value of this character is questionable. Apart from the male of 
<taxonomicName id="3FF64D7F4973FF9265E9FF68FED9FF03" baseAuthorityName="O. P. Cambridge" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[251,381,224,248]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Zelotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helvolus">
<emphasis id="CA82EAEE4973FF9265E9FF68FED9FF03" box="[251,381,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="239">C. helvolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a female was collected from the same locality which is identical to that described as 
<taxonomicName id="3FF64D7F4973FF926090FF68FE0BFEE7" authority="(Levy, 1998)" authorityName="Levy" authorityYear="1998" baseAuthorityName="Levy" baseAuthorityYear="1998" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Zelotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helvoloides">
<emphasis id="CA82EAEE4973FF926090FF68FEB3FEE7" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="239">C. helvoloides</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="9C674B0D4973FF926434FE8CFE03FEE7" author="Levy" box="[294,423,260,284]" pageId="2" pageNumber="239" refString="Levy, G. (1998) The ground-spider genera Setaphis, Trachyzelotes, Zelotes, and Drassyllus (Araneae: Gnaphosidae) in Israel. Israel Journal of Zoology, 44, 93 ‾ 158." type="journal article" year="1998">Levy, 1998</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(compare 
<figureCitation id="60CD2A794973FF92673BFE8CFD28FEE6" box="[553,652,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1919,1941]" captionTargetBox="[165,1420,605,1851]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,600,1877]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Cryptodrassus helvolus (O. P. Cambridge, 1872). 1. Male left palp, ventral view. 2. Same, retrolateral view. 3. Same, prolateral view. 4. Same, dorsal view. 5. Epigyne. 6. Vulva. Co: conductor. Arrows show the two chambers of spermathecae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1002544/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="239">Figs 5, 6</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="60CD2A794973FF9267D6FE8CFD7BFEE7" box="[708,735,260,284]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1564,1586]" captionTargetBox="[173,1407,692,1505]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,657,1543]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 11. Cryptodrassus helvoloides (Levy, 1998) – Holotype (7 ̅ 10) and female paratype (11). 7. Habitus. 8. Eye region. 9. Maxillae and chelicerae. 10. Left palp, ventral view. 11. Epigyne." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1002546/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="239">11</figureCitation>
of present paper with 
<bibRefCitation id="9C674B0D4973FF9266CDFE8DFBCBFEE7" author="Levy" box="[991,1135,260,285]" pageId="2" pageNumber="239" refString="Levy, G. (1998) The ground-spider genera Setaphis, Trachyzelotes, Zelotes, and Drassyllus (Araneae: Gnaphosidae) in Israel. Israel Journal of Zoology, 44, 93 ‾ 158." type="journal article" year="1998">Levy (1998)</bibRefCitation>
: p. 150, Figs 126̄127). In the original description of 
<taxonomicName id="3FF64D7F4973FF9264DDFEA0FD1BFEBB" authority=", Levy" authorityName=", Levy" authorityYear="1998" box="[463,703,296,320]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Zelotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helvoloides">
<emphasis id="CA82EAEE4973FF9264DDFEA0FDD7FEBB" box="[463,627,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="239">C. helvoloides</emphasis>
, Levy
</taxonomicName>
expressed doubts about the correct matching of the two sexes because they were not found on the same locality. In fact, the female 
<typeStatus id="274D885E4973FF9266A3FEC5FBB5FE9E" box="[945,1041,333,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="239">paratype</typeStatus>
of this species was collected from Nahal Seker in the Negev desert, where 
<taxonomicName id="3FF64D7F4973FF92674BFEF8FD72FE73" baseAuthorityName="O. P. Cambridge" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[601,726,368,392]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Zelotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helvolus">
<emphasis id="CA82EAEE4973FF92674BFEF8FD72FE73" box="[601,726,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="239">C. helvolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was also recorded. In our case, both sexes were captured in the same house yard and they seem to belong to the same species. We therefore propose the transfer of the female 
<taxonomicName id="3FF64D7F4973FF926090FE1CFEB3FE2B" authorityName=", Levy" authorityYear="1998" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Zelotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helvoloides">
<emphasis id="CA82EAEE4973FF926090FE1CFEB3FE2B" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="239">C. helvoloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="3FF64D7F4973FF926428FE30FE1CFE2B" baseAuthorityName="O. P. Cambridge" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[314,440,440,464]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Zelotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helvolus">
<emphasis id="CA82EAEE4973FF926428FE30FE1CFE2B" box="[314,440,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="239">C. helvolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
